<div id="wrapper"><h2><a href="/output/Page2.asp"><img alt="" height="70" src="../files/images/XM_logo.gif" title="XM London Digital Communication" width="162" /></a></h2><h2><img width="190" alt="Case histories" height="80" border="0" src="/files/images/XM_L3_Clients_histories_shdr.gif" /></h2><p><strong>Buckingham Palace</strong></p><p>A key objective was to represent the Monarchy's position as a modern organisation with an unrivalled history. </p><p>The site features five principal sections: The Monarchy Today; The Royal Family; History of the Monarchy; Art and Residences and Insight Magazine.</p><p>The creative challenge was to convey the grandeur and illustriousness of the Monarchy in a clear yet understated way.</p><p>The site, with its dramatic new design, includes everything from sending the Queen a message to applying for a job at the Palace and buying tickets to visit a royal residence.</p><p>There is a children's section where you can paint pictures and a visitors book where you can send messages and join the mailing list.</p><p><a target="_blank" href="http://www.royal.gov.uk">http://www.royal.gov.uk</a></p><p><img alt="Buckingham Palace website" border="0" height="195" src="/files/images/XM_L3_histories_buckingham_1.jpg" width="280" /></p><p><img alt="Buckingham Palace website" border="0" height="195" src="/files/images/XM_L3_histories_buckingham_1a.jpg" width="280" /></p><img class="hide" src="/files/images/clear.gif" width="1" height="1" alt="" />
